## Installation & Setup

Setting up Device Guardian (DG) and Device Guardian Access Management (DGAM) involves installing the required components, configuring devices and ensuring all prerequisites are met. Make sure to review the [Requirements](#requirements) section and refer to the [Installation Notes](#installationnotes) section for important information.

### DG Setup

To set up **Device Guardian (DG),** the following components and steps are required:

- **Device Guardian Client App -** Install the app on the device and enroll it to the server. Refer to the installation instructions specific to your EMM platform within this guide.
- **Optional: Identity Guardian for Single Sign-On (SSO) -** If enabling [SSO](../config/#singlesignonsso) for user accountability, install [Identity Guardian](/identityguardian) v2.0 or higher on devices and configure it with [SSO Authentication Configuration](/identityguardian/latest/mc/#ssoauthenticationconfiguration). For setup instructions, refer to the [Identity Guardian Setup Guide](/identityguardian/latest/setup).

### DGAM Setup

> **This section applies only to DGAM.**

To set up **Device Guardian Access Management (DGAM),** the following components and steps are required:

**For Both Kiosks and Devices:**
- **Device Guardian Client App-** Install the app on kiosks and devices, and enroll them to the server. Refer to the installation instructions specific to your EMM platform within this guide.

**For Devices only:**
- **[Identity Guardian](/identityguardian) Client App -** Identity Guardian is **_required_** for user authentication and device accountability and is essential to operate DGAM. Configure Identity Guardian according to your user authentication strategy. For setup instructions, refer to the [Identity Guardian Setup Guide](/identityguardian/latest/setup).
- **DataWedge Profile -** Use Zebra's DataWedge application to facilitate barcode scanning for DGAM. [Import the DataWedge profile](#importdatawedgeprofile) onto devices to enable kiosk integration.
- **[Register Devices to Kiosk](../setup/#registerdevicetokiosk) -** Enable localized device monitoring and management directly through the kiosk by registering devices to the kiosk system.

**For Kiosks Only:**
- **Assign the [Kiosk](../config/#managekiosks) to a Site -** After enrolling the kiosk to the server, assign it to the appropriate site to enable monitoring and management.
    
---

### Installation Notes

- **<code>Important for Android 11:</code>** For Android 11 devices, _Device Guardian <u>must</u> be launched after installation_ to apply the configurations.
- **Google Play Services update -** During an update, the Android system automatically stops Device Guardian. After the update is complete, relaunch the Device Guardian app or reboot the device to resume device tracking.
- **Config Service Notification -** When configuring Device Guardian client for the first time, a notification appears indicating the Config Service is running. This notification disappears following a subsequent device reboot.
- **Compatibility with Device Tracker -** The Device Guardian server is backward compatible with Device Tracker client apps. However, the Device Tracker client app cannot be upgraded to the Device Guardian client app; a new installation of the Device Guardian client is required.

